						<div class="event-date">2018.11.24 (土) 18:00 – </div>
				
		<h2 class="article-ttl">
			WET - WARE / FAB - FABRIC 第一回目「生命を身につける」 半生命的素材とはなにか イベントレポート
		</h2>
	</a>
	
																									<div class="tag-btn"><a href="/bioclub-org/tags/news">#NEWS</a></div>
		
							<div class="thumb">
				<a href="/bioclub-org/project-report/wet-ware-fab-fabric-1-1" class="ct-block hv-op">
					<span class="img-wrapper"><img src="/bioclub-org/assets/images/wwff01.jpg" alt="WET - WARE / FAB - FABRIC 第一回目「生命を身につける」 半生命的素材とはなにか イベントレポート"></span>
					
																<p class="ct-link-lead">Design researcher Kazuya Kawasaki and Bio Club director Chiaki Ishizuka organized the WET - WARE - / FAB - FABRIC working group to study and practice innovation at the intersection of biotechnology and fashion. The commemorative first meeting reconsidered the concept of conventional &quot;anthropocentric&quot; clothing design and featured Mr. Yohsuke Takahashi, curator at the 21st Century Museum of Contemporary Art, Kanazawa who actively plans bio-art exhibitions.</p>
									</a>
